commit.message:
Skip test_cov if pytest-cov is not installed

Skip test_cov gracefully if pytest_cov module can't be imported.
This would help us since we're removing py2 support from pytest-cov
but still need it for pytest-timeout.
pbd -> pdb
Prepare next release

Fix is_debugging function

It was using `name in <module object>` which is a TypeError. It was working
previously with the builtin pdb because of the pytest_enter_pdb hook which
is triggered by pytest.

Fix compatibility with pytest prereleases

The problem was that StrictVersion from distutils doesn't recognize a release candidate (such as 6.0.0rc1) as a valid version, although it is supported by [PEP-0440](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0440/#pre-releases).

Fix #68

Add test run using pre-releases

This helps testing pytest-timeout with pytest prereleases from now on.
Fix linting

Give some more time to install the debugger

This fails consistently on ci.  Perhaps it's cutting it too short.
Perhaps it's indicative that making this too fast will just lead to
flaky tests.

Speed up test suite by using fractional timeouts

We've supported fractional timeouts for ages.  I finally found a good
use for them, speed up our own test suite by a lot!
Set 1.4.1 version

Fix coverage compatibility

Coverage also installs a tracing function, but it does not have a
__module__ attribute (it's probably written in C?).  Anyway, if we get
stuff we don't know about we don't change behaviour.

Fixes #66
Fix rst admonition formatting
Simplify is_debugging logic
Add pep257 to pre-commit

Disable timing-out when a debugging session is in progress (#62)

Detect external debuggers based on pdb (bdb) and pydevd
